Jose Mourinho's side took an early lead through a rare goal from Ivory Coast defender Serge AurierHarry Kane's 19th goal of the season - the England captain's fourth in his last six games - increased Tottenham's advantage before half-timeDavid McGoldrick got one back for United in the second half, but Ndombele's sublime lob wrapped up the points at Bramall Lane